radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 10 mm with thickened walls, mucosal hyperemia, and mild periappendiceal and right lower quadrant fat stranding. Multiple prominent, likely reactive right lower quadrant lymph nodes are demonstrated. No focal fluid collections or extraluminal gas is seen to suggest perforation. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and adrenal glands demonstrate normal findings. No urinary or reproductive organ abnormalities noted.
